{"node_id": "01161156fd4a542ba4fd1433fff033ee", "title": "Understand: Legislative Branch—Text and History", "description": "Check your understanding of the text and history of the Legislative Branch with this set of multiple-choice questions.", "topic_path": ["Khan Academy (English - US curriculum)", "Arts and humanities", "Constitution 101", "The Three Branches of Government", "Legislative Branch—Text and History", "Understand: Legislative Branch—Text and History"], "assessment_items": [{"item_id": "c1ab4a8154dd5d7a83fa9c92c137ae23", "question_content": "**What is the primary job of the legislative branch? **\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "To make the laws", "correct": true}, {"content": "To enforce the laws", "correct": false}, {"content": "To interpret the laws", "correct": false}, {"content": "To veto the laws", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "c59ef7b7e2f853ddbd53c3cb7f922deb", "question_content": "**It is the responsibility of Congress to \\_\\_\\_\\_.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "veto laws", "correct": false}, {"content": "both make and enforce laws", "correct": false}, {"content": "both enforce and interpret laws", "correct": false}, {"content": "make laws", "correct": true}]}}}, {"item_id": "eb775b79f1f6548b8e783b27a6afd9c4", "question_content": "**Which chamber is the upper chamber of Congress?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "House of Representatives", "correct": false}, {"content": "Court of Appeals", "correct": false}, {"content": "Parliament", "correct": false}, {"content": "Senate", "correct": true}]}}}, {"item_id": "cbc9ef00497c503ea3998c78398d46d9", "question_content": "**What TWO chambers make up Congress?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "House of Representatives", "correct": true}, {"content": "Senate", "correct": true}, {"content": "Parliament", "correct": false}, {"content": "Supreme Court", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "47019b247748545e89af4c7da277074e", "question_content": "**How many members currently serve in the U.S. House of Representatives?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "100", "correct": false}, {"content": "270", "correct": false}, {"content": "435", "correct": true}, {"content": "538", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "b282fe377de25e2c8474fd1686343003", "question_content": "**How many members currently serve in the U.S. Senate?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "100", "correct": true}, {"content": "270", "correct": false}, {"content": "435", "correct": false}, {"content": "538", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "6f194799d8765f5fa569521f6440f751", "question_content": "**According to Article I of the Constitution, which powers belong to Congress? **\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "Declaring war", "correct": true}, {"content": "Laying and collecting taxes", "correct": true}, {"content": "Granting titles of nobility", "correct": false}, {"content": "Granting pardons", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "18da428dfb4952908f790214d6fcf527", "question_content": "**Article I, Section 8, of the Constitution establishes that Congress has the power to make all laws \\_\\_\\_\\_.**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "regardless of the will of the people", "correct": false}, {"content": "that are approved by the president", "correct": false}, {"content": "which are necessary and proper", "correct": true}, {"content": "that are convenient and profitable", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "b396a66a66835250a0761c8c3ec30b8a", "question_content": "**What is an enumerated power?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "A power split between two different branches of government", "correct": false}, {"content": "A power not explicitly mentioned in the Constitution", "correct": false}, {"content": "A power that is named in the Constitution", "correct": true}, {"content": "A power that is reserved for the states ", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "0f4801dcfbca52c095d97d3371001f66", "question_content": "**The bicameral structure of Congress, in which states have equal representation in the Senate and representation based on population in the House of Representatives, is the result of what agreement during the Constitutional Convention?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "The Virginia Plan", "correct": false}, {"content": "The New Jersey Plan", "correct": false}, {"content": "The Connecticut Compromise", "correct": true}, {"content": "The Missouri Compromise", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "0d800ad08b6f5aa780623b17010ef8c1", "question_content": "**What provision of the Constitution is primarily responsible for listing the enumerated powers of Congress?**\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "Article I, Section 1", "correct": false}, {"content": "Article I, Section 8", "correct": true}, {"content": "Article II, Section 4", "correct": false}, {"content": "The Preamble", "correct": false}]}}}, {"item_id": "593d43091c3e51a5b4d01a63d4b7f43a", "question_content": "**Which section of Article I gives “all legislative Powers herein granted” to Congress?**\n\n\n[[☃ radio 1]]\n\n", "hints": [], "widget_types": ["radio"], "answer_data": {"radio 1": {"type": "radio", "choices": [{"content": "Section 1", "correct": true}, {"content": "Section 4", "correct": false}, {"content": "Section 7", "correct": false}, {"content": "Section 8", "correct": false}]}}}], "mastery_model": {"type": "m_of_n", "m": 3, "n": 4}, "randomize": true}